version_description: My version is different because I transposed the key to the key of C so it will be easier for beginners to play.

in most versions a G chord is used in the chorus, i sincerely believe this should be an Em chord. also in other tabs it just says to play the chorus, i personally always like it if i can see the chorus again because i scroll through the song while playing. i also added how to play the chords.

These instructions are for Zevon's posthumously released "Preludes" version of Accidentally Like a Martyr. It has a substantially different feel due to it's situation in a major Key. These instructions are in the key of F# . Despite this it is unclear what key the song is in as the piano, interestingly, may have been tuned a half step up or down one of the traditional keys.
